HEADWORD: Mezuzoth
<hw>Mez"u*zoth</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>m⟦ecr⟧z⟦umac⟧z⟦omac⟧th</ets>, pl. of
<ets>m⟦ecr⟧z⟦umac⟧z⟦amac⟧h</ets> doorpost.]</ety> <def>A piece of
parchment bearing the Decalogue and attached to the doorpost; -- in use
among orthodox Hebrews. The term is also used to refer to the small case
containing this scroll, together with the biblical inscription inside.
The text is usually taken from Deuteronomy 6:4-9 and 11:13-21.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

